passages.text: Novel candidate SNPs for familial AJ breast cancer.

<sup>*</sup>G/C loci: minor allele = G on positive strand.MA=minor allele; MAF=minor allele frequency for Cases (“A”) and Controls (“U”); p-values based on χ<sup>2</sup> test on allele counts or genotype distribution between cases and controls. All 3 datasets were combined for pooled P-values and ORs and Fisher Meta-analysis. Cochran Q and I<sup>2</sup> statistics for heterogeneity are reported (“I<sup>2</sup>/Q”).
Confirmation of known breast cancer variants.

MA=minor allele; MAF=minor allele frequency for Cases (“A”) and Controls (“U”); p-values based on χ<sup>2</sup> test on allele counts between cases and controls. All 3 datasets were combined for pooled P-values and Ors and Fisher Meta-analysis. Cochran Q and I<sup>2</sup> statistics for heterogeneity are reported (“I<sup>2</sup>/Q”).
Previously identified variants for MSKCC dataset (a) and FGFR2 haplotype (b).
